xQTLbiolinks 0.1.0
  • Reference

    xQTLdownload_sqtlSig

    xQTLdownload_sqtlSig.Rd

    download significant sQTL associations of a tissue or across all tissues. Only GTEx v8 is supported.

    Usage

    xQTLdownload_sqtlSig(
  variantName = "",
  gene = "",
  variantType = "auto",
  geneType = "auto",
  tissueSiteDetail = ""
)

    Arguments

    variantName

    A character string. like dbsnp ID or variant id in GTEx.

    gene

    A gene symbol or a gencode id (versioned).

    variantType

    A character string. "auto", "snpId" or "variantId". Default: "auto".

    geneType

    A character string. "auto","geneSymbol" or "gencodeId". Default: "auto".

    tissueSiteDetail

    A character string. tissue detail can be listed using \"tissueSiteDetailGTExv8\" or \"tissueSiteDetailGTExv7\"

    Value

    A data.table

    Examples

    # \donttest{
 # Download sQTL detail for a variant:
 xQTLdownload_sqtlSig(variantName="rs201327123")
